
Overview of noun illusion

The noun illusion has 4 senses (first 3 from tagged texts)
                                       
1. (23) illusion, semblance -- (an erroneous mental representation)
2. (6) illusion, fantasy, phantasy, fancy -- (something many people believe that is false; "they have the illusion that I am very wealthy")
3. (1) delusion, illusion, head game -- (the act of deluding; deception by creating illusory ideas)
4. magic trick, conjuring trick, trick, magic, legerdemain, conjuration, thaumaturgy, illusion, deception -- (an illusory feat; considered magical by naive observers)
